{"text":{"description":[{"type":"text","value":"Gov. Greg Gianforte, elected in Nov. 2020, took office in early 2021 as Montana’s first Republican governor since 2005."},{"type":"text","value":"The governor appoints state agency heads and is ultimately responsible for the day-to-day management of government. The governor also prepares a budget proposal that serves as a starting point for the legislative appropriations process, where lawmakers determine how much the governor’s executive branch is allowed to spend."},{"type":"text","value":"Bills passed by the Legislature are sent to the governor, who can sign them into law, issue a veto, or let them become law without his signature. Vetos can be overridden by two-thirds majority votes in both the House and Senate."}]},"articles":[{"title":"New round of federal COVID-19 aid means billions for Montana","subtitle":"","date":"2021-03-11T00:19:49.000Z","link":"https://montanafreepress.org/2021/03/10/new-round-of-federal-covid-19-aid-means-billions-for-montana/","tags":["2021 Legislature","coronavirus","COVID-19","federal aid","federal stimulus","Greg Gianforte","Joe Biden","montana budget"],"author":"Eric Dietrich","imageUrl":"https://montanafreepress.org/2021/03/10/new-round-of-federal-covid-19-aid-means-billions-for-montana/dollar-stack/","billTags":[],"lawmakerTags":[],"governorTags":["Greg Gianforte"]},{"title":"The Session podcast","subtitle":"","date":"2021-03-08T16:51:12.000Z","link":"https://montanafreepress.org/2021/03/08/the-session-podcast-week-10/","tags":["2021 Legislature","broadband","COVID-19","Greg Gianforte","House Bill 102","House Bill 113","House Bill 121","House Bill 176","House Bill 2","House Bill 230","House Bill 303","House Bill 424","House Bill 427","Income Tax","Llew Jones","minimum wage","Montana Legislature","pandemic","podcast-player","Senate Bill 10","Senate Bill 140","Senate Bill 159","Senate Bill 184","Senate Bill 215","Senate Bill 280","Senate Bill 65","Taxes","The Session","transmittal de